//@version=6
// SolSignal TrendBreak — Pine v6 reference indicator.
//
// Mirrors the Python TrendBreakStrategy entry logic and fires webhook alerts
// in the JSON shape the SolSignal relay expects. Two uses:
//   1) Prototype/visualize strategy tweaks on TradingView charts.
//   2) Drive the experimental webhook bot (#3) via TradingView alerts.
//
// To wire alerts: add this to a chart -> "Create Alert" -> Condition = this
// indicator -> paste the relay URL as the webhook -> the alert() message below
// is sent automatically. Requires TradingView Pro+ (webhooks are paid-only).
//
// SECURITY: replace the secret via the alert message, not in shared code.
//
// REPAINT/LOOKAHEAD AUDIT (2026-07-16, per the AI-trading-bot-playbooks
// research — request.security repaint can fake-inflate a 47% strategy to 61%):
//   - No request.security() is used, so there is no multi-timeframe repaint or
//     lookahead vector here.
//   - Swing levels use high[1]/low[1] (the PRIOR bar), never the forming bar.
//   - Alerts fire with alert.freq_once_per_bar_close, so a signal is only sent
//     on a CONFIRMED close — the intrabar plotshape may flicker, but the traded
//     alert does not repaint.
// If you add higher-timeframe context later, pass lookahead=barmerge.lookahead_off
// to request.security and reference the [1] value.

indicator("SolSignal TrendBreak v6", overlay = true)

swingLen = input.int(20, "Swing lookback bars")
volMult  = input.float(1.5, "Volume x 20-bar avg")
secret   = input.string("PUT_RELAY_SECRET_HERE", "Relay shared secret")

swingHigh = ta.highest(high[1], swingLen)
swingLow  = ta.lowest(low[1], swingLen)
volOk     = volume > volMult * ta.sma(volume, 20)
uptrend   = ta.ema(close, 50) > ta.ema(close, 200)

longBreak = ta.crossover(close, swingHigh) and volOk and uptrend
closeSig  = ta.crossunder(close, swingLow)

plotshape(longBreak, "long",  shape.triangleup,   location.belowbar, color.green, size = size.small)
plotshape(closeSig,  "close", shape.triangledown, location.abovebar, color.red,   size = size.small)

// JSON payloads for the SolSignal relay (POST /webhook). syminfo.ticker gives
// e.g. "BTCUSD"; the relay normalizes it to "BTC/USD".
enterMsg = '{"secret":"' + secret + '","action":"buy","pair":"'   + syminfo.ticker + '"}'
exitMsg  = '{"secret":"' + secret + '","action":"close","pair":"' + syminfo.ticker + '"}'

if longBreak
    alert(enterMsg, alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)
if closeSig
    alert(exitMsg, alert.freq_once_per_bar_close)
